nt Employee - Software Engineer in Draper, UTDoesn't RecommendNeutral OutlookDisapproves of CEOI have been working at Control4 full-time (More than a year)ProsRelaxed, family-oriented environment.The work life balance is great. There some flexibility in the work schedule.The technology is good. Free and discounted equipment is available after a brief period with the company.Occasional lunch provided by the company.Some of the company activities are good.Below management level, some of the people are genuinely sincere, friendly and very helpful.Opportunity to learn different technologies and skills.The quality of pay depends on the individual.ConsUpward mobility from within the company, career growth, bonuses and promotions are practically non-existing.Innovative technology is a figment of one's imagination. Mid management says they encourage this. However, their attitudes and actions prove otherwise.There are toxic people in this environment who seems to poison any progress of existing projects. Furthermore, it seems these people have too much clout in major decision making. Finally, the most loud and obnoxious people in a meeting room will be heard over more reasonable voices.The health benefits are sub par.Stock options have been removed as part of the benefits package.The quality of QA is terrible. This organization releases software containing known issues.The organization and its processes are in need of improvements.Mid management and project management are both questionable. There's is lack of and inconsistent vision, direction and planning.The CEO seems to care more about his image than his people, the product and the end consumer.Advice to ManagementHighly talented engineers are very difficult to find, let alone retain. Reward those high performers, and seek to make improvements in order to maintain high morale and loyalty. The toxic people must be removed or entire departments will be destroyed.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (5) Control4 Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Control4 2016-11-22 08:24 PST Sep 21, 2016"Great place to work with cool stuff and outstanding people!"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Senior Firmware Engineer in Draper, UTCurrent Employee - Senior Firmware Engineer in Draper, UTRecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Control4 full-time (More than 5 years)ProsWork is interesting and relevant. Positive environment. Focus is on giving customers amazing home automation solutions. Solving problems emphasized, not finding blame. Pay and most benefits are competitive.ConsNo 401k match. Because of growth related issues, cubicle space is inadequate for some. Stock options discontinued.Advice to ManagementImplement 401k matching. Allocate work space based more on needs. Consider bringing back stock options.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Control4 Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Control4 2016-09-21 11:32 PDT Jun 15, 2016 Helpful (1)"QA test engineer"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - QA Test Engineer in Draper, UTCurrent Employee - QA Test Engineer in Draper, UTRecommendsPositive OutlookNo opinion of CEOI have been working at Control4 full-time (Less than a year)ProsGreat people and fun products to work with. People are friendly and helpful. Management is great and they really appreciate their employees.ConsNone as of yet. Haven't meet with many outside of my immediate group yet. Possible need for additional space/building in the futureAdvice to ManagementKeep innovating and creating the best product in automation. Lots of neat things I think in the futureShare on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on 