 Technical Support Agent in Sandy, UTDoesn't RecommendNegative OutlookDisapproves of CEOI have been working at Control4 full-time (More than 3 years)ProsYou get free gear every year. Coworkers for the most part are fun people to be around.ConsSupervisors are non-existent so many employees take advantage of that. I've had days where i did absolutely nothing for half a day and havent had a supervisor or manager ever take notice. Only 30 minutes for lunch, which is frequently taken away if we have company meetings. Complete lack of leadership in day to day work. QA of products seems subpar, there are frequently known bugs of released software or hardware but it gets pushed out to meet deadlines.Advice to ManagementPay attention to your employees and their daily habits. Forcing others to take on a higher workload because you have half your techs wasting time is ridiculous.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (6) Control4 Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Control4 2015-10-28 14:36 PDT Dec 8, 2014 Helpful (2)"Awesome technology; Leadership that is both human and accessible"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Draper, UTCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Draper, UTRecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Control4 full-time (Less than a year)ProsControl4's technology is amazing. For anyone who wants to work in technology that is actually relevant to their own lives, this may be the best place in Utah. The employee beta program allows you to outfit your own home with company gear, and many industry partners extend amazing accommodation pricing on their gear. The result is that you get to work on things you actually use, and use things you have helped to create.The other thing I love is that management here are not aloof and unreachable like so many other places I have worked. They care about customers, the company, and employees. I can talk to the CEO, VPs of R&D, Sales, or Marketing. They're in touch, and will listen to the ideas of others.ConsHaving lived too long under the start-up mindset, the company is now in a much-needed transition phase. It's becoming more focused and mature in its processes. That means it has some technical debt to pay down, and maturing to do. It's underway, but needs to happen faster.Advice to ManagementDon't allow growth to unmoor you from direct contact with the people who produce, market, sell and support the company's solutions.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Control4 Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Control4 2014-12-08 13:47 PST Showing 29 of 31 reviewsReset FiltersPrevious123NextReviews > Control4 RSS Feed</>Embed Control4 Careers Control4, a leading provider of personalized automation and control solutions, allows you to control virtually any device in a home or...    – More Work Here! Giving Back Utah Rocks!This is the employer's chance to tell you why you should work for them. The information provided is from their perspective.Reviews by Job TitleSoftware Engineer (5) Engineer (2) Technical Support Agent (2)  Company BenefitsHealth InsuranceAdd BenefitsSee AllSee All Job Seekers Also ViewedInstructure ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 178 Reviews4 Control ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 1 ReviewsOverstock.com ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 703 ReviewsinContact ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 191 ReviewsIntermountain Healthcare ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 630 ReviewsMasterControl ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 29 ReviewsO.C. Tanner ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 152 ReviewsDomo ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 236 ReviewsExperticity ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 51 ReviewsSpace Dynamics Laboratory ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 39 ReviewsClearlink ReviewsStarStarStarStarStar 297 ReviewsImagin